  "prompt": "What percentage of questions are yet to be answered in Quora?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, Quora has not publicly released specific statistics regarding the percentage of questions that remain unanswered on its platform. Quora hosts millions of questions across a vast array of topics, and the dynamics of question-answering can vary widely based on factors such as topic popularity, question clarity, and the engagement of the Quora community.\n\nHowever, it's common for large Q&A platforms like Quora to have a mix of answered and unanswered questions. Several factors influence whether a question receives answers, including:\n\n1. **Topic Popularity:** Questions in well-covered or popular topics are more likely to be answered.\n2. **Question Clarity:** Clear, well-formulated questions tend to attract more responses.\n3. **Community Engagement:** Active communities with knowledgeable users can lead to higher answer rates.\n4. **Timing:** Newer questions might not have received answers yet, while older ones may remain unanswered.\n\nIf you're interested in the current state of unanswered questions on Quora, you might consider the following approaches:\n\n- **Explore Specific Topics:** Visit particular topics of interest to gauge the activity and response rates.\n- **Engage with the Community:** Participating by answering questions can help reduce the number of unanswered queries and increase overall engagement.\n- **Monitor Quora's Updates:** Keep an eye on Quora's official blog or announcements, as they occasionally share platform statistics and insights.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, you may also consider reaching out directly to Quora's support or media relations team.",
